'''Season six''' of ''[[Smallville]]'', an [[United States|American]] [[television series]], began airing on September 28, 2006. The series recounts the early adventures of [[Krypton (comics)|Kryptonian]] [[Clark Kent (Smallville)|Clark Kent]] as he adjusts to life in the fictional town of [[Smallville (DC Comics)|Smallville]], [[Kansas]], during the years before he becomes [[Superman]]. The sixth season comprises 22 episodes and concluded its initial airing on May 17, 2007,<ref name="tvg">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/detail/tv-show.aspx?tvobjectid=100398&more=ucepisodelist|title=Smallville Episodes |publisher=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=2007-07-09}}</ref> marking the first season to air on the newly formed [[The CW Television Network|CW]] television network.  Regular cast members during season six include [[Tom Welling]], [[Kristin Kreuk]], [[Michael Rosenbaum]], [[Allison Mack]], [[Annette O'Toole]], [[John Glover (actor)|John Glover]], and [[Erica Durance]].

Season six key story arcs involve Clark (Welling) trying to recapture several escaped criminals from the [[Phantom Zone]], the destinies of Lionel (Glover) and Lex (Rosenbaum) following the aftermath of Lex's possession by Zod and Lionel's adoption as the emissary of Jor-El, and the introductions of [[DC Comics characters]] [[Jimmy Olsen]], [[Oliver Queen]] and [[Martian Manhunter]], played by [[Aaron Ashmore]], [[Justin Hartley]], and [[Phil Morris (actor)|Phil Morris]] respectively. Other key storylines involve Lana and Lex's marriage, as well as Lex's secret 33.1 projects.

''Smallville'''s Season six slipped in the ratings, averaging 4.1 million viewers weekly.<ref name="Rate">{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/television/features/e3ifbfdd1bcb53266ad8d9a71cad261604f|title=2006-07 primetime wrap|publisher=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=2007-05-25|accessdate=2007-05-25 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070528062839/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/television/features/e3ifbfdd1bcb53266ad8d9a71cad261604f <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-05-28}}</ref> It was nominated for an [[Emmy Award]], among other awards, in the category of Outstanding Sound Editing For A Series for the episode "Zod".<ref>{{cite news|author=Brian Thomas|url=http://www.ifmagazine.com/new.asp?article=4752|title=Official Emmy Nominations Announced|publisher=iF Magazine|date=2007-07-19|accessdate=2007-09-10 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20071003090957/http://www.ifmagazine.com/new.asp?article=4752 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-10-03}}</ref>

==Main cast==
*[[Tom Welling]] as [[Clark Kent (Smallville)|Clark Kent]]
*[[Kristin Kreuk]] as [[Lana Lang (Smallville)|Lana Lang]]
*[[Michael Rosenbaum]] as [[Lex Luthor (Smallville)|Lex Luthor]]
*[[Erica Durance]] as [[Lois Lane (Smallville)|Lois Lane]]
*[[Allison Mack]] as [[Chloe Sullivan]]
*[[John Glover (actor)|John Glover]] as [[Lionel Luthor]]
*[[Annette O'Toole]] as [[Characters of Smallville#Martha Kent|Martha Kent]]

