==Awards==
The sixth season was awarded [[Leo Awards]] in multiple categories.  Make-up artist Natalie Cosco was awarded the Leo Award for Best Make-Up for her work on the episodes "Hydro" and "Wither".<ref name="2007 Leo">{{cite web|url=http://www.leoawards.com/winners_2007.html|title=2007 Leo Awards|publisher=LeoAwards.com|accessdate=2007-08-23}}</ref>  The show itself won Best Dramatic Series; James Marshall won Best Direction for "Zod"; Caroline Cranston won Best Costume Design for her work on "Arrow", and James Philpott won Best Production Design for "Justice".<ref name="2007 Leo"/>  The [[American Society of Cinematographers]] honored the series with an award for the work done on "Arrow",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altfg.com/awards/2006/american-society-of-cinematographers.htm|title=2006 ASC Award Winners|publisher=Alternative Film Guide|accessdate=2007-08-23}}</ref> and with an award for Glen Winter for his work on "Noir".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascmag.com/news/awards/awards_history.php#2007|title=22nd Annual ASC Awards <U+2014> 2007|publisher=[[American Society of Cinematographers]]|accessdate=2008-08-15}}</ref> Mack won Best Sidekick for the second year in a row when she took home the award in the 2007 Teen Choice Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fox.com/teenchoice/winners/|title=2007 Teen Choice Award Winners|publisher=Fox|accessdate=2007-08-27 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070830111612/http://www.fox.com/teenchoice/winners/ <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-08-30}}</ref> The series was recognized by the [[Visual Effects Society]] with a 2007 VES Award nomination for Outstanding Visual Effects in the episode "Zod".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vesawards.com/5thvesnominee.pdf|title=5th Annual VES Awards|publisher=[[Visual Effects Society]]|accessdate=2007-09-10}}</ref> The VES recognized the season in 2008, nominating "Justice" for Outstanding Compositing in a Broadcast Program or Commercial.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visualeffectssociety.com/downloads/NomineesPressRelease2008.pdf|title=VISUAL EFFECTS SOCIETY (VES) ANNOUNCES NOMINEES FOR 6TH ANNUAL VES AWARDS|publisher=VES.com|date=2007-01-07|accessdate=2007-01-07}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>  In 2007, the sound effects and foley teams were nominated for a [[Golden Reel Award]] for Best Sound Editing for their work on "Zod".<ref name="GReel">{{cite web|url=http://www.mpse.org/goldenreels/pastawards.html|title=Past Golden Reel Awards|publisher=MPSE.org|accessdate=2007-09-11}}</ref><!--GOLDEN REEL PUTS THEIR PREVIOUS WINNERS LIST ON IMDB.COM, PLEASE SEE GR CITATION FOR VERIFICATION.!--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/Sections/Awards/Motion_Picture_Sound_Editors_USA/2007|title=2007 Golden Reel Awards|publisher=Internet Movie Database|accessdate=2007-09-11}}</ref>  David Moxness won the [[American Society of Cinematographers]] Outstanding Achievement in Cinematography Award for his work on "Arrow".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altfg.com/awards/2006/american-society-of-cinematographers.htm|title=21st ASC Awards|publisher=Alternative Film Guide|accessdate=2007-09-11}}</ref>  In the 33rd Annual [[Saturn Awards]], the show was nominated for Best Dramatic Television Series, as well as a Best Supporting Actress nomination for Allison Mack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/8250|title=33rd Annual Saturn Award nominees|publisher=Bloody Disgusting|date=2007-02-20|accessdate=2007-09-13}}</ref>

